__HEADER__
.SH NAME
restauth-user \- Utility to manage users in RestAuth.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B restauth-user
[options] \fIaction\fR \fIargs\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
The purpose of \fBrestauth-users\fR is to manage basic aspects of users in
RestAuth. This includes adding users, setting their password and removing them.
You can also use \fBrestauth-users\fR to view detailed information on a user and
verify the users password.

To manage the groups a user is in, use \fBrestauth-groups\fR(8).
.SH OPTIONS
.RS 4
.RE
__SETTINGS_OPTION__
\fB\-\-password\fR=\fIPWD\fR
.RS 4
Use \fIPWD\fR for the password for actions \fBadd\fR, \fBset-password\fR and
\fBverify-password\fR. If you do not use this option for these actions, you will
be prompted interactively.
.SH ACTIONS
.sp
With each invocation of \fBrestauth-users\fR you can give exactly one action.
.sp
\fBadd\fR \fIusername\fR
.RS 4
Add a user with the username \fIname\fR to RestAuth. The characters that
\fIusername\fR may contain depends on the configuration. See the
\fBSKIP_VALIDATORS\fI settings in \fBsettings.py\fR.

If you don't specify the password with the \fB--password\fR option, you will be
prompted for it interactively.
.RE
.sp
\fBlist\fR
.RS 4
List all users.
.RE
.sp
\fBview\fR \fIusername\fR
.RS 4
View details on the user identified by the username \fIusername\fR.
.RE
.sp
\fBset-password\fR \fIusername\fR
.RS 4
Set the password of the user identified by the username \fIusername\fR.

If you don't specify the password with the \fB--password\fR option, you will be
prompted for it interactively.
.RE
.sp
\fBverify-password\fR \fIusername\fR
.RS 4
Verify the password of the user identified by the username \fIusername\fR.

If you don't specify the password with the \fB--password\fR option, you will be
prompted for it interactively.
.RE
.sp
\fBremove\fR \fIusername\fR
.RS 4
Remove the user identified by the username \fIusername\fR
.RE
.sp
\fBhelp\fR \fIaction\fR
.RS 4
Give the help-text on one of the \fIactions\fR named above.
.RE
__END__
